section.t:
An RDAP server returns the registrant entity in a subentity, which makes difficult to parse given the expectation is the registrant would be at the top level. Extract of the response: 

{
 entities: [ 
  { 
    "objectClassName": "entity",
    "handle": "HANDLE1",
    "roles": [ "abuse" ], 
    "vcardArray": [ ... ],
    "entities": [
       {
       "objectClassName": "entity",
       "handle": "HANDLE2",
       "roles": [ "registrant" ], 
       "vcardArray": [ ... ],
       }
    ],
],

   Recommendation: put the registrant in the top-level entities as follows:

{
 entities: [
  { 
    "objectClassName": "entity",
    "handle": "HANDLE1",
    "roles": [ "abuse" ],
    "vcardArray": [ ... ]
  },
  {
    "objectClassName": "entity",
    "handle": "HANDLE2",
    "roles": [ "registrant" ],
    "vcardArray": [ ... ],
  }
],
